Delta of Zimbabwe Operating Income Rises 76% as Sales Climb

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-05-12T14:10:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/delta-of-zimbabwe-operating-income-rises-76-as-sales-climb-1-.html
Delta Corp. Ltd.,  Zimbabwe ’s largest
brewer, reported a 76 percent surge in operating income for the
year through March.  The Harare-based company, Zimbabwe’s biggest by market
capitalization, reported an attributable profit after tax and
deductions of $53 million, 47 percent more than in the previous
financial year.  Operating income increased to $68.2 million, Africa
Corporate Announcements said in a statement today from Harare,
the capital. Revenue climbed 45 percent to $408 million while
earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortization
rose 67 percent to $81.7 million.  Delta Corp. also produces Coca-Cola products under license
in Zimbabwe. The company sells its bottled products in Zimbabwe
and exports beer to neighboring countries. Delta is 36 percent-
owned by London-based  SABMiller Plc. (SAB)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban,  South Africa  at 
